text.pre: The operation this command will execute

choice.choiceText: creates and configures a new object
adds a child object to the one specified by the -handle param
modified attributes on the given object by the -handle param
deletes the object given by the -handle param

text.pre: The parent handle used for creating this object. Has the form: /vport/protocolStack/ethernet/dcbxEndpoint/range/dcbxRange
A handle returned via a ::<namespace>::dcbxtlvqaz_config command. This is used for mode modify
The IxNetwork object typepath that is created after the command is run. Is optional in most cases. Only applies to modes create/add
Specifies if this TLV is used in the configuration.

Type code of the DCB Feature. The codes translate to: 2 - Priority Group 3 - PFC 4 - Application (IEEE 1.01) / Custom(BCN) (Intel 1.0) 5 - Custom (IEEE 1.01) / FCoE (Intel 1.0) 6 - Custom (IEEE 1.01) / Logical Link (Intel 1.0) 7 - NIV 8 - Custom (IEEE 1.01 / Intel 1.0) 9/10 - Custom (IEEE 1.01 / Intel 1.0) / ETS Configuration/Recommendation (802.1Qaz) 11 - Custom (IEEE 1.01 / Intel 1.0) / PFC (802.1Qaz) 12 - Custom (IEEE 1.01 / Intel 1.0) / Application Priority (802.1Qaz) 13 to 127 - Custom (IEEE 1.01 / Intel 1.0)
